properties.Name: InsurancePolicyReducedAmountPaidUpInsurance
properties.Description:
A form of insurance available as a non-forfeiture option that provides that the cash value of the insurance policy be used as a single premium to purchase additional paid-up insurance in whatever amount the cash value will provide.

In most cases the cash value will be less than the original face amount of the insurance policy.

Columns.Name: ReducedPaidUpInsuranceDate
Columns.Description: The date that the paid-up insurance values are calculated 'as-of'.

Columns.Name: InsurancePolicyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Policy.

Columns.Name: ReducedPaidUpInsuranceFaceAmount
Columns.Description: The original face amount of the insurance policy.

Columns.Name: ReducedPaidUpInsuranceCashPayment
Columns.Description: The reduced paid-up insurance amount as of the associated date.
